            <thetext>We have sometimes stored constants in classes. These constants are mostly attached directly to the javascript class object by defining them in the statics block of the class definition. This make it hard to show a warning if somebody accesses them.
A solution, at least for newer browsers could be to define a getter for them via __defineGetter__ , which is supported by modern browsers. (https://developer.mozilla.org/En/Core_JavaScript_1.5_Guide:Creating_New_Objects:Defining_Getters_and_Setters)</thetext>
